column11: CHEM 105 is the laboratory course that accompanies CHEM 104. Engineering students must obtain a dean's approval to drop this course after the second week of instruction. CHEM 104 and CHEM 105 are approved for General Education credit only as a sequence. Both courses must be completed to receive Natural Science and Technology credit.
